f=Engineering/rank/custom/technical-seo-execution/SKILL.md · in=technical-seo-execution rank's core craft: making site crawlable, indexable, technically sound search engines (and answer engines) find, render, understand it. Crawl directives, canonicalization, sitemaps, redirects, status codes, rendering, mobile, Core Web Vitals mechanical foundation under SEO. rank owns execution; kai owns whether it's right strategy. · p=best content ranks nowhere search engines can't crawl it, index wrong version, hit wall 404s redirect chains. Technical SEO plumbing invisible works, catastrophic doesn't `noindex` shipped production tanks whole site). rank keeps plumbing sound kai's strategy lena's content actually rank. · wu=Triggers: "technical SEO," "why isn't indexed," "crawlability," "canonical," "sitemap," "robots.txt," "redirect," "status codes," "rendering SEO," "mobile SEO," any technical ranking-foundation issue. · st:/ Protocol=`A technical SEO task \· -> CRAWLABILITY: robots.txt correct \· no accidental blocks \· crawl budget sane \· internal linking \· -> INDEXABILITY: canonical tags \· no accidental noindex \· correct indexation status \· -> SITEMAPS: accurate XML sitemap \· submitted \· matches indexable reality \· -> STATUS & REDIRECTS: right codes (200/301/404/410) \· no redirect chains/loops \· fix soft-404s` · in=**Crawlability before anything.** Confirm robots.txt doesn't accidentally block important paths, internal linking lets crawlers reach content, crawl budget isn't wasted junk (faceted URLs, infinite spaces). blocked path invisible regardless quality. **Indexability canonical.** page correct canonical (self intended master); accidental `noindex` pages rank (the classic catastrophe staging `noindex` shipped live). Verify actual indexation status, don't assume. **Accurate sitemaps.** XML sitemap lists indexable URLs (not redirects, noindexed, 404s), submitted, matches reality sitemap full dead URLs erodes trust crawlers. **Correct status codes, clean redirects.** 200 live, 301 permanent moves, 404/410 gone; redirect chains (301→301→301) loops; fix soft-404s (200 "not found" page). waste crawl budget confuse indexing. **Rendering frontend seam.** Content present crawlers; client-rendered SPA shows crawlers empty shell doesn't rank (the JS-rendering issue trips naive scraping). mia seam SSR/prerendering/hydration joint fix, rank specs SEO requirement. **Mobile-first Core Web Vitals.** site judged mobile-first; Core Web Vitals (INP interactivity, retired FID) ranking signal shared mia rank owns SEO framing measurement-of-record kai, mia owns making them good. rank diagnoses specs; builders implement through normal gate. · of=`## Technical SEO: [site/page] \· Crawlability: [robots ✓ \· reachable ✓ \· crawl budget] \· Indexability: [canonical ✓ \· no stray noindex ✓ \· status] \· Sitemap: [accurate + submitted ✓] \· Status/redirects: [codes ✓ \· no chains/loops \· soft-404s fixed] \· Rendering: [content visible to crawlers ✓ / SSR gap → mia] \· Mobile + CWV (INP): [ready / issues → mia] \· Findings → implementation: [mia / raj \· dev review \· quinn gate] (rank specs, doesn't auto-edit)` · pr=**Crawlability first** blocked path invisible regardless quality., **Guard canonical noindex** stray noindex tanks site; verify indexation, don't assume., **Sitemaps match indexable reality** dead-URL sitemaps erode crawler trust., **Clean status codes redirects** chains, loops, soft-404s wasting crawl budget., **Rendering frontend seam** crawlers see content; SSR joint mia fix., **rank specs, builders implement** silent production edits; through review gate. · f=plugin (claude-seo absent) method carries technical SEO fully, labeled reduced-automation; plugin deepens present., Rendering/SSR gap needs framework change spec SEO requirement, hand mia/dev architecture question (it ADR)., Conflicting canonical/strategy signals confirm intended master kai (strategy owner) before setting canonicals. · b:with Other Skills=**kai (Brand Studio)**: strategy measurement; rank executes technical foundation (seo-ownership-boundary)., **claude-seo-integration** (sibling): plugin deepens this; rank's method without it., **structured-data-geo** (sibling): schema AI-search readiness build foundation., **mia**: rendering/SSR Core Web Vitals joint (shared signal); rank specs SEO need, mia implements., **raj**: server-side redirects, status codes, headers, SSR infrastructure., **dev/quinn**: technical SEO changes pass review gate; noindex/robots change high-risk fragile-area regression-map candidate).